"Through memory we travel against time, through forgetfullness we follow it's course."
	-- Joseph Joubert, The Notebooks: 1789-1794

Then let us rail against the course of time.

Liquor, then, must be the very nectar of time. This alone explains why so much of it requires aging as it does: to imbue it with the properties of timem most necessary to elicit this forgetfullness. 
